Project Full Name:         Comag Stream Converter
Project Unix Name:         tscomagcv
SVN Server:                svn.berlios.de/svnroot/repos/tscomagcv/trunk
Web Server:                tscomagcv.berlios.de
Project Short Description: Documentation of the files of Comag PVR2/100CI
                           aka Silvercrest SL80/2 100CI.
Project Members:           Markus Kohm (Admin) <mjk at users.berlios.de>
Status:                    "1 - Planning" up to "2 - Pre Alpha"

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Project Long Description:
-------------------------

The records of Comag PVR2/100CI or Silvercrest SL80/2 100CI are folders
rec_DDDD (DDDD is a four digit decimal number) with MPEG TS files rec.ts,
rec.01, rec.02 ..., and additional informations at a file meta.dat, rec.cp and
rec.bm.  The MPEG TS files has a special format with header and padding
sequences.  First purpose of this project is documentation for all these
files.  Second pupose are some programs to analyse, gernate or manipulate the
records.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Directory Organization:
-----------------------

The files of the project are organized at directories:

doc/          - all the documentation
+- doc.latex/    - documentation in LaTeX format
|  +- Makefile        - create other formats from the LaTeX format
|     index.tex       - the start file for the LaTeX documentation
+- doc.html/  - documentation in HTML format
|  +- index.html      - the start file for the HTML documentation
+- doc.pdf/   - documentation in PDF format

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

How to checkout the source from SVN:
====================================

You may checkout the source using SVN access or HTTP access.

Anonymous SVN Access via SVN:
-----------------------------

Use the command:

    svn checkout svn://svn.berlios.de/tscomagcv/trunk

to checkout the current sources of the project to the current working
directory.

Anonymous SVN Access via HTTP:
------------------------------

Use the command:

    svn checkout http://svn.berlios.de/svnroot/repos/tscomagcv/trunk

to checkout the current sources of the project to the current working
directory.

How to update your local working copy:
======================================

After the first checkout you may update your local working copy simply by
entering the directory with the local working copy and use:

    svn update

